data.chText: （船舶或飞机发出的）紧急呼救信号
data.enText: a signal or message that a ship or plane sends when it needs urgent help

data.chText: 我们收到来自那一地区的紧急求援信息，他们急需食物包。
data.enText: We've received an SOS from the area asking for food parcels.

means: (船舶或飞机发出的)紧急呼救信号

value.def: An SOS is a signal which indicates to other people that you are in danger and need help quickly.

example.ex: The ferry did not even have time to send out an SOS.
example.tran: 渡船甚至连发出紧急呼救信号的时间都没有。
